description:
mrigger added on 2020-10-02 21:16:20:
Consider the following test case:
CREATE TABLE t0(c0);
INSERT INTO t0(c0) VALUES (0);
CREATE VIEW v1(c0, c1) AS SELECT CAST(0.0 AS NUMERIC), COUNT(*) OVER () FROM t0;
SELECT v1.c0 FROM v1, t0 WHERE v1.c0=0; -- expected: {0.0}, actual: {0}

It seems unexpected that the result is an integer, rather than a real. When removing the WHERE clause, the result is as expected:
SELECT v1.c0 FROM v1, t0; -- {0.0}
